The paper deals with the performance analysis of error-correcting codes, specifically quadratic residue codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses decoding algorithms and their performance, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of simulations and mathematical theorems to analyze the performance of the codes suggests a focus on computational complexity and algorithms, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
